    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "No, that's expected behaviour - that's why the default `str` functions currently return `NaN` for missing or non-string values. The `na` parameter allows to choose a mapping (usually it makes sense to set it as `False`, but you can pick any other convenient value to avoid the contradiction, if necessary).\r\n\r\nBear in mind that you always have `isnull()` and `notnull()` for filtering, so it's straightforward to simply run `Series.str.isalpha().notnull()` as your filter."
